title: Červený Kameň Castle with its Italian influences is the place to go
itunes:author: The Slovak Spectator
itunes:summary:
It is not only a furniture museum. The well-preserved fortress, hidden in the Small Carpathians, is home to a replica of Madonna of Bruges and breathtakingly huge cellars. Explore this covert and cozy place with Englishman James Thompson.
 
Presenter: Peter Dlhopolec
